[+1016] World's Deepest Living Fish Caught On Film at 24,800 Feet
item.description: A species of snail fish--the deepest living fish in the world--have been captured on camera n the southern hemisphere for the first time. These strange, pink-bodied fish were photographed at a stunning depth of 24,800 feet in the Kermadec Trench off the coast of New Zealand.

item.title: [+752] 33 Awesomely Futuristic OLED Design Concepts
item.description: OLEDs are like a new type of magical material, self-illuminating and eco-friendly. They are organic and work in a way similar to the bioluminescence that makes a firefly and certain deep sea fish glow. OLEDs can be extremely thin, flexible, varying in shapes, colors and sizes, some are even transparent while providing a lovely ambient glow.
